Non-sensitive configuration files are managed using Docker Configs. These configurations are version-controlled and mounted into contt[36;1Hainers at runtime.

[35m### [m[35mConfigs include:[m
[38;5;130m-[m Traefik configuration[40;116H103,1[9C60%[20;1H[?25h[?4m[?12$p[?25l[40;106H/[20;1H[40;107H0[20;1H[40;108Hc[20;1H[40;109H0[20;1H[40;110Hc[20;1H[40;111H/[20;1H[40;112H0[20;1H[40;113Hc[20;1H[40;114H0[20;1H[40;115Hc[20;1H[40;106H          [20;1H[27m[23m[29m[m[H[2J[1;3HNetwork connecting the frontend service with Traefik.

[93m-[m [1m**backend**[m (internal)
  Internal network used by backend microservices. This network is not accessible externally.

[93m-[m [1m**data**[m (internal)
  Dedicated internal network for databases and stateful services.

[93m-[m [1m**monitoring**[m
  Network reserved for observability and monitoring components.

Services are attached only to the networks they require, preventing unauthorized access between layers.

[38;5;81m---[m

[38;5;224m## [m[38;5;225m4. Secrets Management[m

All sensitive information is managed using Docker Secrets to avoid hardcoding credentials in configuration files or version control.

[38;5;224m### [m[38;5;225mSecrets include:[m
[93m-[m Database root and application passwords
[93m-[m JWT signing keys
[93m-[m Redis authentication password
[93m-[m RabbitMQ credentials
[93m-[m MinIO secret keys
[93m-[m Grafana admin password
[93m-[m TLS private keys (if applicable)

Secrets are injected into containers at runtime and never stored in images or source code.

[38;5;81m---[m

[38;5;224m## [m[38;5;225m5. Configuration Management[m

Non-sensitive configuration files are managed using Docker Configs. These configurations are version-controlled and mounted into contt[36;1Hainers at runtime.

